import capacityspecificationsummarytypedef def get_value() -> capacityspecificationsummarytypedef: return {...} ``` ## how it works fully automated [mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `boto3` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `boto3` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `boto3` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and `aioboto3` libraries - `mypy`, `pyright`, discovery of types for `client.get_waiter` and `client.get_paginator` calls - auto discovery of types for `serviceresource` and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in [releases](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder/releases). ## versioning `mypy-boto3-keyspaces` documentation_summary: The HTML text is about "mypy-boto3-keyspaces," a Python package available on PyPI (Python Package Index) that provides type annotations for the boto3.Keyspaces service. The latest version, 1.34.45, was released on February 19, 2024. This package, generated with mypy-boto3-builder version 7.23.1, is designed to enhance code quality and developer productivity by enabling better type checking and auto-completion in various IDEs (Integrated Development Environments) such as VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, and Sublime Text. It requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. The package supports a wide range of Python versions, from 3.8 to 3.13, and is compatible with CPython. It offers explicit type annotations for client and paginator usage, literals for type checking, and type definitions for additional type checking. The package is part of a broader effort to provide fully type-annotated boto3, botocore, aiobotocore, and aioboto3 libraries, with compatibility across major Python tools and IDEs.
